Paper: hep-th/0202196

Date: 2002-02-27

Title: Hamilton - Jacobi treatment of front-form Schwinger model

Authors: D. Baleanu, Y. Guler

Comments: 11 pages, to be published in Int. Journ. Mod. Phys. A

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A17 (2002) 1449

The Hamilton-Jacobi formalism was applied to quantize the front-formSchwinger model. The importance of the surface term is discussed in detail. TheBRST-anti-BRST symmetry was analyzed within Hamilton-Jacobi formalism.